 1. A sacrifice wholly consumed by fire; a whole burnt offering.     2. ''transf.'' and ''fig.''    a. A complete sacrifice or offering.    b. A sacrifice on a large scale.   c. Complete consumption by fire, or that which is so consumed; complete destruction, esp. of a large number of persons; a great slaughter or massacre.     d. ''the Holocaust:'' the mass murder of the Jews by the Nazis in the war of 1939-1945. Also used ''transf.,'' of the similar fate of other groups; and ''attrib.''